Class HourOfWeek

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count.BaseCount<HourOfWeek>
com.telenav.kivakit.core.time.HourOfWeek
All Implemented Interfaces:
Countable, NextValue<HourOfWeek>, Sized, MapFactory<Long,​HourOfWeek>, Arithmetic<HourOfWeek>, Castable, CastTrait, DoubleQuantizable, IntegerNumeric<HourOfWeek>, Maximizable<HourOfWeek>, Minimizable<HourOfWeek>, Quantizable, Stringable, StringSource, Source<Long>, Comparable<HourOfWeek>, Supplier<Long>
public class HourOfWeek extends BaseCount<HourOfWeek>
Represents an hour of the week, for example Thursday at 1pm. This class stores its count value in the fields dayOfWeek() and hourOfDay(), and it overrides asLong() to provide a count value to the superclass based on those two fields.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
